<ext_description linkend="Design_management_arm">
</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ Add_design_object_management_relationship +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Design_management_arm.Add_design_object_management_relationship"><p>
An <b>Add_design_object_management_relationship</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Product_view_definition_relationship:arm:Product_view_definition_relationship_arm.View_definition_relationship"/>.
</p><note>
Together with  <express_ref linkend="Design_management:arm:Design_management_arm.Change_design_object_management_relationship"/> and
 <express_ref linkend="Design_management:arm:Design_management_arm.Delete_design_object_management_relationship"/>,
<b>Add_design_object_management_relationship</b> supports the exchange
of changes to a design by the use of a data set containing only
(1) the information necessary to identify the design, such as, an
 <express_ref linkend="Product_view_definition:arm:Product_view_definition_arm.Product_view_definition"/> or an  <express_ref linkend="Product_version:arm:Product_version_arm.Product_version"/>, which is assumed
to be already known to the receiving system, and (2) the design
objects that have been added, changed, or deleted.  All
the quality and structural requirements defined in this part of ISO 10303
may also apply to the resultant new design iteration.
</note>
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Design_management_arm.Add_design_object_management_relationship.current_design_object">
specifies the role for the <b>Add_design_object_management_relationship</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Design_management_arm.Add_design_object_management_relationship.ur:UR1">
The <b>current_design_object</b> shall be unique within a population 
of <b>Add_design_object_management_relationship</b>.
</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ Change_design_object_management_relationship +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Design_management_arm.Change_design_object_management_relationship">
A <b>Change_design_object_management_relationship</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Product_view_definition_relationship:arm:Product_view_definition_relationship_arm.View_definition_relationship"/>.
A <b>Change_design_object_management_relationship</b> may be a <express_ref linkend="Functional_decomposition_to_design:arm:Functional_decomposition_to_design_arm.Terminal_swap_specification"/>, or a <express_ref linkend="Functional_decomposition_to_design:arm:Functional_decomposition_to_design_arm.Gate_path_swap_specification"/>, or a <express_ref linkend="Functional_decomposition_to_design:arm:Functional_decomposition_to_design_arm.Component_swap_specification"/>.
 The <b>Change_design_object_management_relationship</b> provides information about the relationship between a design object before and after a design change. 
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Design_management_arm.Change_design_object_management_relationship.previous_design_object">
specifies a  <express_ref linkend="Design_management:arm:Design_management_arm.managed_design_object"/> from which the current design was derived.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Design_management_arm.Change_design_object_management_relationship.current_design_object">
specifies a  <express_ref linkend="Design_management:arm:Design_management_arm.managed_design_object"/> which resulted from a design change.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Design_management_arm.Change_design_object_management_relationship.ur:UR1">
The combination of the <b>current_design_object</b> shall be unique within a population 
of <b>Change_design_object_management_relationship</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Design_management_arm.Change_design_object_management_relationship.ur:UR2">
The combination of <b>previous_design_object</b> shall be unique within a population of <b>Change_design_object_management_relationship</b>.
</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ Delete_design_object_management_relationship +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Design_management_arm.Delete_design_object_management_relationship"><p>
A <b>Delete_design_object_management_relationship</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Product_view_definition_relationship:arm:Product_view_definition_relationship_arm.View_definition_relationship"/>.
Together with  <express_ref linkend="Design_management:arm:Design_management_arm.Change_design_object_management_relationship"/> and
 <express_ref linkend="Design_management:arm:Design_management_arm.Add_design_object_management_relationship"/>,
<b>Delete_design_object_management_relationship</b> supports the
exchange of changes to a design by the use of a data set
containing only (1) the information necessary to identify the
design (e.g., an  <express_ref linkend="Product_view_definition:arm:Product_view_definition_arm.Product_view_definition"/> or an  <express_ref linkend="Product_version:arm:Product_version_arm.Product_version"/>),
which is assumed to be already known to the receiving system, and
(2) the design objects that have been added, changed, or deleted.
</p><note>
Note that all the quality and structural requirements defined in
this part of ISO 10303  also apply to the resultant new design
iteration.
</note>
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Design_management_arm.Delete_design_object_management_relationship.previous_design_object">
specifies the role of the  <express_ref linkend="Design_management:arm:Design_management_arm.managed_design_object"/> for the 
<b>Delete_design_object_management_relationship</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Design_management_arm.Delete_design_object_management_relationship.ur:UR1">
The combination of the <b>previous_design_object</b> inherited from  <express_ref linkend="Product_view_definition_relationship:arm:Product_view_definition_relationship_arm.View_definition_relationship"/> shall be unique within a 
population of <b>Delete_design_object_management_relationship</b>s.
</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ Design_object_management_relationship +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Design_management_arm.Design_object_management_relationship">

A <b>Design_object_management_relationship</b> is one of an <express_ref linkend="Design_management:arm:Design_management_arm.Add_design_object_management_relationship"/>, a <express_ref linkend="Design_management:arm:Design_management_arm.Change_design_object_management_relationship"/>, or a <express_ref linkend="Design_management:arm:Design_management_arm.Delete_design_object_management_relationship"/>. A <b>Design_object_management_relationship</b> specifies the relationship between the original design and a design change via the <express_ref linkend="Product_view_definition:arm:Product_view_definition_arm.Product_view_definition"/>.
</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ View_dependent_design_object_management_relationship +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Design_management_arm.View_dependent_design_object_management_relationship">
A  <b>View_dependent_design_object_management_relationship</b> is a type of an <express_ref linkend="Design_management:arm:Design_management_arm.Design_object_management_relationship"/>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Design_management_arm.View_dependent_design_object_management_relationship.current_design">
specifies the current <express_ref linkend="Product_view_definition:arm:Product_view_definition_arm.Product_view_definition"/>, after the change, for the  <express_ref linkend="Product_view_definition_relationship:arm:Product_view_definition_relationship_arm.View_definition_relationship"/>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Design_management_arm.View_dependent_design_object_management_relationship.previous_design">
specifies the <express_ref linkend="Product_view_definition:arm:Product_view_definition_arm.Product_view_definition"/>, before the change, for the  <express_ref linkend="Product_view_definition_relationship:arm:Product_view_definition_relationship_arm.View_definition_relationship"/>.
</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ Design_object_management_relationship_assignment +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Design_management_arm.Design_object_management_relationship_assignment">
A <b>Design_object_management_relationship_assignment</b> is a mean to relate <express_ref linkend="Product_view_definition_relationship:arm:Product_view_definition_relationship_arm.View_definition_relationship"/> 
with <express_ref linkend="Design_management:arm:Design_management_arm.design_object_management_relationship_item"/>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Design_management_arm.Design_object_management_relationship_assignment.items">
specifies the  <express_ref linkend="Design_management:arm:Design_management_arm.design_object_management_relationship_item"/> for the <b>Design_object_management_relationship_assignment</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Design_management_arm.Design_object_management_relationship_assignment.changes">
specifies the  <express_ref linkend="Product_view_definition_relationship:arm:Product_view_definition_relationship_arm.View_definition_relationship"/>, for the <b>Design_object_management_relationship_assignment</b>.
</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ Frozen_assignment +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Design_management_arm.Frozen_assignment">

 A <b>Frozen_assignment</b> is the specification that one or 
more <express_ref linkend="Design_management:arm:Design_management_arm.managed_design_object"/> must be unchanged during further design activity.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Design_management_arm.Frozen_assignment.frozen_item">
specifies a  <express_ref linkend="Design_management:arm:Design_management_arm.managed_design_object"/>
for which the design is to remain unchanged in the <b>Frozen_assignment</b>. 
There shall be one or more  <express_ref linkend="Design_management:arm:Design_management_arm.managed_design_object"/> for a 
<b>Frozen_assignment</b>.
</ext_description>
</ext_descriptions>

